(1797, 187, 'home_aca_content_02', '<b>The result will be a risk pool that must be funded by the collective premiums of the remaining 50-499 FTE private-sector employers in the fully insured health market.</b>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Cook Group Solutions</b></em> specializes in administering the health benefits and providing medical stop-loss insurance for private-sector employers transitioning from fully insured benefits to self-insurance.\r\n\r\n<em>1. Source: Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality, Center for Financing, Access and Cost Trends. 2013 Medical Expenditure Panel Survey-Insurance Component.</em>'),
(1798, 187, '_home_aca_content_02', 'field_54da5671a5777'),
(1799, 188, 'home_list_title', 'Protection. Flexibility. Access. <span></span>'),
(1800, 188, '_home_list_title', 'field_54d4dffe77262'),
(1801, 188, 'home_main_content', '<b>Since 1974, Cook Group has been a leading provider</b> of third party administration (TPA) services and medical stop-loss insurance products to the private-sector employer marketplace.'),
(1802, 188, '_home_main_content', 'field_54d4de99acaa5'),
(1803, 188, 'home_content', 'We work with employers/plan sponsors, <a title="Producer web pages" href="http://localhost:8888/cgs-old/producers/"><em class="lightblue">brokers, agents, and benefit consultants</em></a> to provide self-insured employers with comprehensive health benefits administration combined with financial protection from large and catastrophic claim occurrences.'),
(1804, 188, '_home_content', 'field_54da333be11a5'),
(1805, 188, 'home_acada_title', ' <h2>ACA <span class="one">Affordable</span><span class="two">Care</span><span class="three">Act</span> <span class="border"></span></h2>'),
(1806, 188, '_home_acada_title', 'field_54da34216f306'),
(1807, 188, 'home_aca_content', 'The passage of the 2010 Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act (‘ACA’) has created a paradigm where companies with fewer than 500 full-time equivalent (‘FTE’) employees may realize substantial benefits by replacing their fully insured medical benefits with self-insured health benefit plans.\r\n\r\n<b>The ACA changes the fully insured market substantially beginning in 2014, but many of the changes do not apply to self-insured plans.</b> Today<sup>1</sup>, 83.9% of private-sector employers with 500+ FTE employees are already self-insured so the impact of the increased risk sharing under the ACA will be particularly acute in the 100-499 and the 50-99 FTE employee segments, as only 25.3% and 13.3% of these companies were self-insured as of 2012, respectively.'),
(1808, 188, '_home_aca_content', 'field_54da35035ec28'),
(1809, 188, 'home_aca_content_02', '<b>The result will be a risk pool that must be funded by the collective premiums of the remaining 50-499 FTE private-sector employers in the fully insured health market.</b>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Cook Group Solutions</b></em> specializes in administering the health benefits and providing medical stop-loss insurance for private-sector employers transitioning from fully insured benefits to self-insurance.\r\n\r\n<em>1. Source: Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality, Center for Financing, Access and Cost Trends. 2013 Medical Expenditure Panel Survey-Insurance Component.</em>'),
(1810, 188, '_home_aca_content_02', 'field_54da5671a5777'),
(1823, 190, 'self_funging_title', 'Fully Insured versus Self-Funded'),
(1824, 190, '_self_funging_title', 'field_54d8c97eff471'),
(1825, 190, 'self-funging_content', '<div class="col-xs-24 content-info">\r\n<p class="text">In a traditional fully insured health plan, your company pays a monthly premium, fixed for a year, based on the number of employees enrolled in the plan. The insurer collects the premiums and pays the health care claims based on the benefits in the policy you purchased. The covered persons are responsible to pay any deductible amounts or co-payments required for covered services under the policy.</p>\r\n<p class="text">The cost of a self-funded plan has fixed components similar to an insurance premium, e.g., administration fees, stop- loss premium, plus variable costs (the claims expenses). The administrative fees and stop-loss premiums are referred to as fixed costs and are billed monthly based on plan enrollment just like an insurance premium. These costs typically range between 15-25% of a comparable fully-insured premiums.  Submitted claims are reviewed by Cook Group, and approved claims are then funded and paid by the employer/plan sponsor without insurance carrier markup, reserves funding and state mandated taxes.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>'),
(1826, 190, '_self-funging_content', 'field_54d8cc76bac1e'),
(1827, 190, 'self-funging_title_employers', 'Not just for large employers'),
(1828, 190, '_self-funging_title_employers', 'field_54d8d1598bf29'),
(1829, 190, 'self-funging_content_employers', '<p class="text">The regulatory complexities of the <strong>Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act</strong> (“ACA”), coupled with double-digit fully-insured health care premium increases, has created an environment where smaller employers (i.e. 50-500 employees) are effectively utilizing self-funding to minimize the administrative burden of offering comprehensive health benefits while controlling, and in many instances, reducing their overall healthcare costs.</p>'),
(1830, 190, '_self-funging_content_employers', 'field_54d8d3ee4f96b'),
(1831, 190, 'self-funging_title_Handling ', 'Handling a catastrophe doesn\'t have to be chaotic'),
(1832, 190, '_self-funging_title_Handling ', 'field_54d8d51ad763f'),
(1833, 190, 'self_funging_content_handling', '<p class="text-italy-strong">Stop-loss medical insurance is a type of coverage that provides insurance protection to employers who choose to self-fund their employee health benefit plans. Sometimes, costly health disasters do happen.</p>'),
(1834, 190, '_self_funging_content_handling', 'field_54d8e04cfe21b'),
(1835, 190, 'self-funging_title_plan', '<h2 class="title"><span>Creating</span>Your Self-Funded <span>Plan</span></h2>'),
(1836, 190, '_self-funging_title_plan', 'field_54d8ed513a4a9'),
(1837, 190, 'self-funging_content_plan', '<div class="col-xs-24 content-info no-pad">\r\n<p class="text">The flexibility of self-funding helps employers use their health benefit plans the way they were originally intended – to attract and retain the finest employees in their respective industry.</p>\r\n<p class="text">As benefits administration specialists, Cook Group helps to design and document the plan, administer all claims on behalf of the covered group, and issue claims payments on behalf of the employer. When Cook Group establishes a self-funded plan for a smaller employer, we guide them to select appropriate levels of stop-loss or excess-loss insurance, which provides reimbursement for large catastrophic and/or a high frequency of claims. Stop-loss insurance protects smaller employers to allow them to pursue this economical approach to providing employee health benefits. <a href="http://localhost:8888/cgs-old/self-funding/#">Read about the benefits of self-insuring with Cook Group Solutions.</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>'),
(1838, 190, '_self-funging_content_plan', 'field_54d8ed8d19011'),
(1839, 190, 'self_funging_content_hand', 'Stop-loss medical insurance is a type of coverage that provides insurance protection to employers who choose to self-fund their employee health benefit plans. Sometimes, costly health disasters do happen.'),
