(5303, 650, 'home_main_content', '<b>Since 1974, Cook Group has been a leading provider</b> of third party administration (TPA) services and medical stop-loss insurance products to the private-sector employer health benefits marketplace.'),
(5304, 650, '_home_main_content', 'field_54d4de99acaa5'),
(5305, 650, 'home_img_top', '18'),
(5306, 650, '_home_img_top', 'field_54d4e54fb0580'),
(5307, 650, 'home_main_content_2', '<div class="col-xs-24 col-sm-12"></div>'),
(5308, 650, '_home_main_content_2', 'field_54d50e238bc7d'),
(5309, 650, 'home_list_title_2', ''),
(5310, 650, '_home_list_title_2', 'field_54d50e3257754'),
(5311, 650, 'home_content', 'We work with employers/plan sponsors, <a title="Producer web pages" href="//localhost:3002/cgs-old/producers/"><em class="lightblue">brokers, agents, and benefit consultants</em></a> to provide self-insured employers with comprehensive health benefits administration combined with financial protection from large and catastrophic claim occurrences.'),
(5312, 650, '_home_content', 'field_54da333be11a5'),
(5313, 650, 'home_acada_title', '<h2>ACA <span class="one">Affordable</span><span class="two">Care</span><span class="three">Act</span> <span class="border"></span></h2>'),
(5314, 650, '_home_acada_title', 'field_54da34216f306'),
(5315, 650, 'home_aca_content', 'The passage of the 2010 Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act (‘ACA’) has created a paradigm where companies with fewer than 500 full-time equivalent (‘FTE’) employees may realize substantial benefits by replacing their fully insured medical benefits with self-insured health benefit plans.\r\n\r\n<b>The ACA changes the fully insured market substantially beginning in 2014, but many of the changes do not apply to self-insured plans.</b> Today, 83.9% of private-sector employers with 500+ FTE employees are already self-insured so the impact of the increased risk sharing under the ACA will be particularly acute in the 100-499 and the 50-99 FTE employee segments, as only 25.3% and 13.3% of these companies were self-insured as of 2013, respectively<sup><span style="font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 20px;">1</span></sup>.'),
(5316, 650, '_home_aca_content', 'field_54da35035ec28'),
(5317, 650, 'home_aca_content_02', '<b>The result will be a risk pool that must be funded by the collective premiums of the remaining 50-499 FTE private-sector employers in the fully insured health market.</b>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Cook Group Solutions</b></em> specializes in administering the health benefits and providing medical stop-loss insurance for private-sector employers transitioning from fully insured benefits to self-insurance.\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h6><em><span style="color: #000000;">1. Source: Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality, Center for Financing, Access and Cost Trends. 2013 Medical Expenditure Panel Survey-Insurance Component.</span></em></h6>\r\n</blockquote>'),
(5318, 650, '_home_aca_content_02', 'field_54da5671a5777'),
